sql:
SELECT activity_description
FROM work_activity
WHERE activity_status = 'Completed';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT employee_id)
FROM work_activity
WHERE location = 'Eastern';

SELECT employee_id, AVG(activity_duration) AS average_duration
FROM work_activity
GROUP BY employee_id;

external_knowledge:
- "sailed through the ocean of productivity" metaphorically refers to employees completing work activities;
- "tasks for more than an hour" refers to activities with a duration of more than 60 minutes;
- "in the first month of 2022" means activities between '2022-01-01' and '2022-01-31';
- "voyages they undertook" refers to the activities the employees completed;
- "ships they sailed on" metaphorically refers to the devices used by employees;
- "anchors they dropped" is used metaphorically to refer to the logons during the activities.

sql:
SELECT AVG(working_days_working_hours) AS average_daylight_hours
FROM work_activity
WHERE location = 'Remote' AND non_working_days > 5;

external_knowledge:
- "tall figures in the workforce" refers to employees who have achieved a certain status; 
- "sprinkle more gold than the average in their garden of departments" means employees earning more than the average salary in their department;
- "castle they serve in" refers to the role of the employee;
- "contributions have been crowned as completed" indicates the activity status is 'Completed'.
